flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Daily schedule horizon (nightly/early-morning) or an exception event from execution (material short, machine downtime, large deviation).]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest master orders, inventory, capacity, changeover matrix and latest work-order actuals.]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS + Data Quality & Validation - Validate data quality and assemble planning subject area; compute derived metrics (available material, effective capacity).]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Process (Process Builder) + Remote Functions (optimizer) - Run deterministic scheduling optimizer (sequence-aware, changeover-minimizing) and generate candidate schedule scenarios.]
  N3 --> N4{PB: CWB Lifecycle + Process IF (Rules) - Evaluate candidate against release rules; auto-approve if no hard violations, else create CWB exception with recommended mitigation.}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Process Transaction node + Remote Functions - Write final approved schedule back to SAP S/4HANA and publish to MES; log transactions and create audit trail.]
  N5 --> N6[UI: UI Screens (dashboard) + Notification (Process Builder) - Surface schedule, KPIs (adherence, changeover minutes, capacity utilization) and exception list to planners/operators and notify stakeholders.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Consistent, capacity‑aware daily schedules released on time; minimized changeover time and sequence-driven efficiency; fewer manual adjustments on the shop floor; improved on-time delivery and reduced inventory/working capital.]
  N4 -->|Material shortages or critical MRP vi...| B1[Hold schedule release, open CWB exception with suggested replan (shift production or substitute parts), trigger procurement alerts and a re-run of optimizer with constrained inputs.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Schedule withheld until mitigation or approved exception; procurement and planners aligned to resolve shortages to avoid execution failures.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Hard capacity or sequencing constrain...| B2[Present alternative schedule scenarios that minimize changeover impact, route to planner/engineer via CWB for approval, and await human decision before writeback.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Prevents infeasible releases; planners choose the preferred compromise minimizing COGS and delivery impact.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Execution deviation (machine downtime...| B3[Trigger asynchronous reschedule subprocess (short-horizon deterministic re-optimization) and push updated sequence/times to MES; notify operations and planners.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Autonomous containment and re-sequencing minimize ripple effects, maintain OTIF and reduce WIP buildup.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]